Signal averaging approach:

All trials were averaged together and the mean amplitude was calculated for each condition for each subject. Subject and electrode were used as crossed random factors. ICCs were first calculated with an intercept-only model.

A model was fitted with Race predicting mean amplitude calculated in this way. The intercept and slope of Race were allowed to vary by subject. The intercept was allowed to vary by Electrode.

Race was effect coded.

## Saving 7 x 5 in image
Simple slopes

Trial is scaled to range from 0 to 10 (instead of 1 to 256) so that the betas associated with trial are a little bigger (but significance testing is unaffected by linear scaling, so the test statistics and p values will be the same as if we used the unscaled Trial variable).

## 2  -0.0536 0.0225    -0.0987   -0.00859 White
